            <div class="ui-content willScroll AboutContent">
                <div data-role="collapsible-set" data-corners="false" >
                <fieldset data-role="collapsible"  >
                    <legend>Why Favorites?</legend>
                    <p>Flashback's learning algorithm ensures that over time you will see more and more cards that you rate Hard, and fewer and fewer cards that you rate Easy.  In this way, Flashback creates your own personalized favorites lists.<br><br>
                    But this can take some time.  Maybe you're browsing along and find a few cards that you want to drill right now?  No problem.  You can save any card as a Favorite, and then select the Favorites deck to study only the cards you have saved.</p>
                </fieldset>
                <fieldset data-role="collapsible"  >
                    <legend>Saving as Favorite</legend>
                    <p>Open the answer field of any card and scroll to the bottom.  Tap the plus (+) icon and the card will be saved to Favorites.  If you instead see a minus (-) icon, the card is already saved to Favorites.  Tap the minus icon to remove it from Favorties.  Either action will prompt a confirmation message.  And either action can be undone simply by tapping once again.</p> 
                
