    <div data-role="page" id="hint19" data-title="Hint: Boot Camp" data-theme="a">

<!--             <div class="whitebar"></div>
            <div class="redbar"></div>
            <div class="whitebar"></div> -->
            <br>

            <div class="ui-content willScroll AboutContent">
                <div data-role="collapsible-set" data-corners="false" >
                <fieldset data-role="collapsible"  >
                    <legend>About Boot Camp</legend>
                    <p>Walter Trice's <a href='#' onclick="window.open('http://www.fortuitouspress.com/bootcamp', '_system', 'location=no')"><em>Backgammon Boot Camp</em></a> began as a series of online columns for GammonVillage, later to become argueably the most highly-regarded and best-selling backgammon book of its time.  Each short chapter introduces a concept such that a beginner can follow, but then develops that concept over five or so pages to places unfamiliar to many experts.  In this way, the book is accessable and informative to everyone.  (The dry humor and graceful clarity of the prose also help.)<br><br>
                    These decks include every position from Backgammon Boot Camp and more.  Find the position name at the bottom of the exposed answer text.
                    <ul>
                        <li>"BBC1-08" is Chapter 1, Position 8.</li>
